Description: Within every empty space is an opportunity for success, a chance to find out who you are in this strange unforgiving world. It's too bad you'll never see it.
It's a lot of small metal blocks squished together into a larger, small metal block.
Stolen from the concrete dome the seals the harmful gas below.
Snaps, crackles, and pops. This is the type of energy that makes your chest hair tingle.
While disgusting to look at. The goo within actually has a pleasant, albeit winter time aroma with notes of musk and cedarwood.
These are famous for being able to grind even the grittiest material into small, awful salad toppers.
Magnetic power consumes these blocks, feel their energy as you snap and piece them back together. You don’t have to say it… feels good right.
A possible torture device used on unfortunate souls unlucky enough to crank it's handles.
There’s nothing that says gritty tech noir more than a slightly rusty chain fence stolen from the backyard.
Rumble, grumble, rumble, POW! They’re off!
It’s not much of a game without a checkmate. Chess without it’s king, baseball without a final inning, not forgetting a loved one within the deep confines of a couch…
Structural support gives way to the future, a cool cross between two beams. Without one each other they feel rather lost, but together, they are whole.
While it may look a little goofy, they’re often used for communication between experiments. Just make sure you’re tuned in and you might catch something.

[MEMO]: I’m afraid I’ve lost my ships last wing, while I may not have much longer to live.  Tell my wife and kids farewell. The ship is currently on a downwards trajectory spiraling uncontrollably. I hope this parting memory does not go to waste, as I have discovered the-
Girders are a staple of a good time. A show of might and force. The wonders of engineering brought to you by a couple beams and a poor weld.
*CHHH* WHERE’S THE BRAKES *CHHH*
It’s a wad of junk…
Pressed through the center, your inedible waste turns into a fine, delicate spaghetti.
A metal tank which burns superior charcoal within.

As he scampered into the grassy knoll underneath a putrid perscotto tree, the small scrungoid asked diligently what this was, beeps and boops filled his head as a pixelated mosaic  reflected off of his multiple eye holes... The father nested deep within roots entangled and winding between the cracks of asphalt below began to rise. He let out a slow chuckle while nodding, “You’ll find out when you’re older”.
Shaken, not stirred.
If you’re going to drown your sorrows, at least remember to live within the walls of your own glass house.
Freshly popped acrylamide.
Cheaply produced Glass which protects you from the outer reaches of the cosmos. [WARNING: Wear safety visors/life jacket when near COSMIC GLASS]
When you have to drop your digested lunch, there’s a place to store that. Keep the atmosphere clean and safe from septic pollution. Thank you.
A cheap knockoff version of an actual light gun.
A city for germs, a micro-colony.
May your sorrows be plentiful
